There are several different associations at BPDC details on each of them are given below:

IEEE (Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers) Chapter at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: This Branch is to foster the technical knowledge among students from all walks of life. "Does not matter what degree are they pursuing, all the students are eligible to join IEEE as a student member so long as they are pursuing a degree with 50% of the Full time. It's a world wide established technical society, not to mention its the biggest of course" The IEEE Student Branch of BPDC is one of the largest IEEE student branches in UAE Section. It organizes competitions and invites eminent scholars and successful entrepreneurs for talks. Students from the Campus participate in IEEE Xtreme which is a 24-hour online International Programming Competition held every year. Faculty In-charge of IEEE is Dr.Nilesh Goel. Chairperson of IEEE is Mohammed Sulaiman. Vice-Chairperson of IEEE is Irfaan Ahmed Khazi.

ACM (Association for Computing Machinery) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: The Association for Computing Machinery is a vibrant and technology-focused association. The association regularly holds coding workshops, bootcamps, hackathons and talks with the objective of introducing students to the latest technologies and for students to share their knowledge and to upskill. There are four special interest groups for students with a focus in specific areas: ACM-CP for Competitive Programming, ACM-HEX for Security and ACM AI for AI, ACM-Dev for Development. ACM BPDC was awarded the excellence award for outstanding chapter activities by ACM headquarters in New York in April 2020. Faculty In-charge of ACM is Dr. Sujala D Shetty. President of ACM is Aditya Saxena. Vice President of ACM is Anmol Deepak Kumar

ACM-W at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: ACM-W BPDC is the women in tech chapter of ACM at BPDC. It aims to inspire and lead women in tech by offering services and programmes for professional and career development. ACM-W contributes to a community of women in tech, through webinars, hands-on sessions, and social media, and by organizing activities such as, seminars, workshops and hackathons. Faculty In-charge of ACM-W is Dr. Sujala D Shetty

SAE Chapter: SAE COLLEGIATE CHAPTER BITS-PILANI is formed under the Mechanical Department BITS-Pilani. The club has been formed to undertake various practical activities going around the world. The purpose of this organization is to provide its members opportunities to gain broader insight into the engineering profession by sponsoring meeting that will bring practicing engineers to the campus, arranging field trips to research and engineering establishments, sponsoring student projects of engineering interest, and participating in local SAEINDIA Section activities. All students attending BITS-PILANI who are SAEINDIA student members or SAEINDIA members are qualified to become members of this organization irrespective of his/her year and discipline.

Association of Electronics Engineers (AOEE) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: Association of Electronics Engineers promotes knowledge and awareness in the field of electrical and electronic engineering through meetings, discussions, quizzes, and other activities, and encourages students to develop their interpersonal skills, confidence, communication skills, and knowledge by conducting presentation competitions, etc. Association of Electronics Engineers students develop a healthy competitive spirit by competing with students from other departments in intra-university events. Faculty In-charge of Association of Electronics Engineers is Dr. Sujala D Shetty. Co-Chairperson of Association of Electronics Engineers is Nausheen Nakhawa. Co-Chairperson of Association of Electronics Engineers is Anuragh Dasgupta

American Institute of Chemical Engineers (AIChE) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: AIChE (American Institute of Chemical Engineers)- the student’s chapter is one of the first American Institute of Chemical Engineers Student Chapters set up in the region. A subchapter is active in organizing industrial field trips, interactive sessions with professionals, and workshops which equip our chemical engineering graduates with hands-on experiences to excel in their careers and to connect to chemical engineers from around the globe. Students involve themselves with networking, such as with students from American Institute of Chemical Engineers chapters at the University of Utah and Brigham Young University, UC Berkeley, and Universidad Nacional de Colombia, as well as mentoring opportunities, and essential educational/career guidance. Faculty In-charge of American Institute of Chemical Engineers is Dr. Murchana Changmai. President of American Institute of Chemical Engineers is Swastik Nagrikar

Skyline at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: SKYLINE’s mission is to educate and empower students for what lies beyond academics. SKYLINE students have membership in the American Society of Civil Engineers (ASCE). Guest lectures and invited speeches by eminent personalities from the construction industry, as well as site visits to leading companies in the industry and organizing workshops offering hands-on experience on popular concepts such as GIS and modern surveying methods, dominate the association’s main activities. Skyline periodically conducts a techfest ‘Constructo’ at the Institute’s Technofest to focus on the gamification of concepts related to the structural design of bridges, soil and transport engineering. Faculty In-charge of Skyline is Dr. Akshay Venkatehwaran. President of Skyline is Sarat Gireesh. Vice President of Skyline is Mohammad Arham Khan

Society of Women Engineers (SWE) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: The Society of Women Engineers (SWE), a U.S.- based global organization with more than 80 affiliates worldwide, advocates for women to have a permanent place and voice in the engineering profession. BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus, is an affiliate campus of SWE and the first dedicated engineering and technology institute in the United Arab Emirates to partner with SWE. BPDC aims to further SWE’s vision of a world with gender parity and equality in engineering and technology. BPDC SWE aims to further promote women’s participation in the fields of science, technology, engineering and mathematics (STEM) by supporting them in spreading their vision and mission and providing them with the necessary skills to compete in the outside world, whether pursuing a master’s degree or as part of the engineering workforce. As part of SWE, the BPDC hosts a variety of events that will empower female students through public speaking and leadership workshops, industry visits, peer-mentored projects, elevator pitches, and networking with other women leaders. Faculty In-charge of SWE is Dr R Swarnalatha

Women In Engineering (WIE) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: IEEE Women in Engineering (WIE) is the largest international professional organization dedicated to the advancement of women engineers and scientists. The mission of IEEE WIE is to facilitate the global recruitment, retention, and recognition of women in engineering disciplines. BPDC WIE is an affinity group that connects with its members through various platforms such as summits, social networks - Facebook, Youtube - and conferences and workshops. Faculty In-charge of WIE is Dr R Swarnalatha. President of WIE is Inas Riyaz Mohammed

Editorial Board at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: The Editorial Board of BPDC oversees publication of the semesterly newsletter, @bitsdubai and the student journal Perspectives. @bitsdubai- A digital edition of the newsletter is published every semester to inform stakeholders about the institution’s events, activities, and achievements. Perspectives- The student journal is a digital publication for students and by students and mainly contains the writings and contributions of the students. It provides them a wonderful platform to showcase their talent as writers and to express their thoughts, feelings, and actions. The Editorial Board consists of student editors, reporters, and graphic designers, headed by a Faculty Editor-in-Chief and patronized by the Director of the Institute. Every year, in September, a screening round is conducted by the Board to select new student members with strong writing, editing, graphic design and interpersonal skills. Faculty In Charge of Editorial Board: Dr. Shazi Shah Jabeen

Center for Innovation, Incubation and Entrepreneurship (CIIE) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: The Center for Innovation, Incubation and Entrepreneurship is a centre that seeks to foster entrepreneurship among students and provide support to translate ideas into successful ventures. The Center for Innovation, Incubation and Entrepreneurship strives to create events and initiatives to bring together young minds to “Ideate, Innovate and Implement”. The Center for Innovation, Incubation and Entrepreneurship enrolls student members based on requirements of the centre. Student members assist in events and help startups under the centre Contact Dr. Aakash Ashok Kamble, +971 4 275 3700 Ext. 213; Room# 120 aakash@dubai.bits-pilani.ac.in

American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: The American Society of Mechanical Engineers Chapter of the Campus in association with the Pinnacle Knowledge Group hold the biggest Student Professional Development Conference (SPDC). SPDC is an initiative of the American Society of Mechanical Engineers to enhance and develop the technical and leadership skills amongst the engineers worldwide. This Student section also organizes various student competitions every year in which many local universities participate. Faculty In-charge of American Society of Mechanical Engineers is Dr. Vincent Shantha Kumar/Dr. Gulshan Kumar. Student In-charge of American Society of Mechanical Engineers is Manjari Mishra

Clubs & Associations at BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus

Student Clubs are formed around academic and national themes to add to the rich mosaics of student life. Students who have common interest in debating come together to form a debating club; those committed to traditional life come together to form a club for preservation of culture and so on. At present BPDC has 15+ students clubs including Dance Club, Music Club, Art and Craft Club, Photography Club, Drama Club, Science and Technology Club, Debating Society, Management Club, Quiz Club, F1 Club, Social Activities, Pixel, Literary Club, Environment Club, etc. The aim of such clubs is to enrich the social and cultural life on the Institute campus.

Club Costs: Most clubs charge a small yearly membership fee ranging from 10-40AED this enables the clubs to hold more fun and entertaining events.

You can join multiple clubs. So, feel free to join as many clubs as you like.

For creating your own club:

a. Criteria: - Uniqueness, written proposal to Dean of Student Welfare. Evaluated based on activities in one semester prior to application of becoming a club. 

b. Procedure:-

1. Submit proposal to Associate Dean of Student Welfare. 

2. Panel of three, consisting of the Dean of Student Welfare, Faculty in charge proposing the club and any other faculty excelling in the respective field, will evaluate the proposal.

The following positions/designations apply to most Clubs in BITS Pilani Dubai Campus

A. President - 4th Year Student

B. Vice President - 3rd Year Student

C. General Secretary - 3rd or 2nd year Student

D. Treasurer - 2nd Year Student

There are several other creative, marketing, sponsorship, and design roles as well, which vary from club to club.

1457e436-867d-40ef-a134-3f4f46545288.text:
There are several different clubs at BPDC details on each of them are given below:

Sports Club: The Sports Club is committed to the health and well-being of the student community. It encourages students and faculty to be involved in recreational sports through intramural, extramural competitions and tournaments. BSF (BITS Sports Festival) is the marquee event of the Sports Club. Faculty In Charge of Sports Club: Dr. Rafiuddin

The Social and Environment Club (MAD- Making A Difference): Social and Environment club organizes many activities throughout the year, some of the major activities being Organic Farming, Making Newspaper Paper Bags to save environment, Mental Health Awareness Workshop, Daan Utsav – Joy of Giving Week, English Classes - English classes are organized regularly to help the supporting staff improve their language skills. ‘MINDFULNESS’ Workshop, Pink Day to create awareness about Breast Cancer, Christmas Breakfast for the members of the supporting staff ,Spectrum-An event to spread happiness amongst the special needs children, Bag of Love - an event to appreciate the efforts of the support staff and security, Valentine’s Day celebration, International Women's Day celebration, DEWA Walkathon on occasion of Earth hour, Dubai Cares Walk for Education ,Earth Day celebration, Dandiya Night, Blood Donation Camps and Teacher's Day. Faculty In Charge of MAD: Dr. Geetha

The Public Speaking and Literary Club: The Public Speaking and literary club as the name suggest is involved in organizing Literary activities such as Debate Competitons, Poetry competitions etc. They also take part in many interuniversity competitions such as Toastmasters debate contest, BITSMUN the Model United Nations (MUN), Emirates Environmental Group Speaking Competition being some of the major events. Faculty In Charge of Public Speaking and Literary Club: Dr Sayantan Chakraborty

Dance Club (Groove): The Dance Club organizes and takes part in many inter and intra university competitions in both categories, Western and Eastern for solo, duet and group dances. They also give invited performances in various events of the institute like Alumni meet , Program at Indian Consulate,   Spectrum, Annual Day and Diro’s Tea Party etc. Faculty In Charge of Dance Club: Dr. V Kalaichelvi

Drama Club (Paribasha): The Drama club, Paribhasha encourages budding actors and performers to showcase their talents by giving them a platform by hosting events during inter and intra university competitions. Events like Proscenium, Standup comedy, Mad Ad, Nukkad Natak (Street Play), A Twist in the Tale, Theatre Competitions and BITS Film Festival are organized by the club. Faculty In Charge of Paribasha: Dr. Geetha

Art Club (Shades): Art Club organizes an exhibition ARTEX every year where students, faculty and staff participate with great enthusiasm. It’s main event is Kalakriti, an Art  exhibition,  a   show case  of various forms of art like Oil painting,  Acrylic painting, Water Colour painting , Poster Colour painting, Digital Art, Classroom art, Pencil Sketching, Oil pastels, Pen/ink art, Pencil color shading, Glass painting, Fabric painting, Embroidery, Pot designs, Best out of Waste (Junk Art) . During Artex, competitions like Rangoli making, Face painting, Henna designing, Origami, Clay modelling, Beg-borrow-steal, Blind art, Doodle god, etc are held. They proactively do decorations for Institute events like Convocation, Alumni Meet, Gandhi Jayanti, Faculty Get Together, Pink Day, and Diwali etc. Faculty In Charge of Shades: Dr.Vijaya Ilango

Music Club (Treble/Trebel): The Music club Trebel of BITS Pilani Dubai campus organizes Musical Events during intra university cultural festival SPARKS and interuniversity event JASHN every year. The Club organizes events such as – Solo and Duet Singing both in Eastern & Western categories, Beat boxing, Band and Instrumental Competition etc. They participate in various inter-university festivals, namely IMT Vaudeville at the Institute of Management and Technology, Watt-fest at Heriot Watt University, Manipal carnival at the Manipal Institute of Technology and at Jashn  organized by BITS Pilani Dubai Campus. The club members perform during many events at the institute like, Ice-Breakers, Annual Day, Diro’s Tea Party etc. Faculty In Charge of Treble: Dr.Rafiuddin

Design Club: The club has been contributing in many ways such as Graphic Design & Illustration done for various events organized by different associations and clubs of the institute. The club is also involved in designing bulletin, brochures pamphlets, for various events like Jashn, Sparks BSF etc. They design the year book for the passing out batch every year. Faculty In Charge of Design Club: Dr. Pranav Mothabhau Pawar

Fashion Club (Allure): the club actively participates in inter and intra university events and organizes various events during Fashion show. Some of the events being Drape- which is a fashion designer's show, Mr & Ms. Sparks where the students compete with each other for the title. Faculty In Charge of Allure: Dr. R. Swarnalatha

Photography Club (Reflexions): The club covers many events like Jashn, Sparks, Recharge, Bits Sports Festival, Enginuity, Technofest, and also covers various Talks and workshops held by all the disciplines of the Institute. A photography competition is also organized by the club during ENGINuity the Technical Festival of BITS Pilani Dubai Campus. They also organize Short film competition. Faculty In Charge of Reflexions: Dr. Amaranath

Quiz Club (Flummoxed): The Quizzing club of BITS Pilani – Dubai Campus, Flummoxed, promotes and creates a quizzing culture on campus by conducting numerous quizzing events, weekly quizzing sessions, and organizes quiz competitions in association with multiple corporate and academic entities. Some of them being, TAPMI Quiz on The Beach, Pop Fiesta, The Big Oh Quizzards by Flummoxed, Lights, Camera, Quiz, Quiz Du Fromage, Tata Crucibles etc. Faculty In Charge of Flummoxed: Dr. Shamshad Ahmad Khan

Supernova Club: The Astronomy Club, SUPERNOVA- was revived recently. It is all about the world beyond ours. The main aim of the club is to bring together Bitsians interested in astronomy and quantum physics. The club will be holding different activities like Lectures, interactions, star gazing sessions, astrophotography, telescope making and workshops, space center visits, infotainment events and sessions on space and quantum physics. The club has a strong designing, marketing, and media team for a smooth functioning and execution of the club activities and for conduction of its events. Faculty In Charge of Supernova: Dr. KK Singh

Wall Street Club: The Wall Street Club (WSC) at BITS Pilani Dubai Campus is a student-run initiative that aims to strengthen the financial knowledge among the students. The club is structurally designed to teach dynamic concepts of finance, economics, and management. The club conducts a series of lecture sessions about various concepts and encourages discussions and debates for further understanding. It provides a platform for interaction and awareness for students to improve their competitiveness and efficiency in the job market. In the past, the club has conducted webinars where industry professionals have been the guest speakers and have delivered talks in their domains of business and cryptocurrency. Faculty In Charge of Wall Street Club: Dr. Sartaj Rasool Rather

Chimera at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: Chimera provides opportunities for Biotech students to participate in fun activities like Agar Painting, Crime Scene Investigation, Poster making competition and many more. Guest lectures and talks are held by professionals in the field, which keep students updated with recent discoveries and developments and provides them with industry exposure. Faculty In-charge of chimera is Dr. DJ. Shariff. Students Representatives of chimera are Joshita Pentapati, Sarah Yusuf, Shreya Suresh

Intelligent Flying Object for Reconnaissance Club (Team IFOR) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: IFOR is a student team engaged in research and development in the field of aerial robotics. Students in electrical and electronic engineering, computer science, and mechanical engineering come together to design and build autonomous and airborne robotic systems. The team’s structure includes artificial intelligence and navigation, computer vision, hardware, and control systems. The team organizes workshops, participates conferences / competitions, and organizes lectures by alumni. Faculty In-charge of IFOR is Dr. V. Kalaichelvi. Student team leaders of IFOR are Kanishkha J, Hafeez Khan

LINUX Users Group at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: The Linux Users group is open and free to all interested BPDC students. The group provides resource material on UNIX Commands and Editor for first year students and installation-related assistance for UBUNTU OS for interested project students. Faculty In-charge of Linux Users Group is Dr. B. Vijayakumar. Core Committee Student Members of Linux Users Group are Dhruv Jain, Ravali Attivilli, Afraa Noureen, Neetesh Singh Bhati, Akshat Raj Sharmam, Harshiv Chandra

Microsoft Tech Club (MTC) at Bits Pilani, Dubai Campus: Microsoft Tech Club is associated with Microsoft Gulf, DIC. It is run by Microsoft Student Partners (MSP), and students of the Microsoft Student Community. Every year the club carries out training programmes for students in emerging technologies using the software tools supplied by Microsoft. Senior members of the club (MSP) undergo training at Microsoft Gulf in Dubai and teach other members of the club about emerging technologies in Computer Science with the support of Microsoft tools whose keys are shared free of cost by Microsoft. MSPs are involved in building applications, training others and social media. They attend seminars, workshops and developer camps at the Microsoft Dubai office. Developers from Microsoft visit and conduct workshops for the members of the club on cutting-edge technologies delivered by Microsoft. The training offered by the club prepares students to in their PS-II program where Microsoft software tools are widely used. Every year the tech club conducts activities like Boot camps, hackathons, technical quizzes, workshops, Code Blitz, Coder of the Year events, and so on. Faculty In-charge of Microsoft Tech Club is Dr. S. Vadivel. President of Microsoft Tech Club is Tanushree Jain
